snippet: Italy on Wednesday allowed 102 migrants, mainly from North Africa and stranded on a tanker in the Mediterranean, to debark on the coast of Sicily.
abstract: Italy allows 102 migrants stranded on a tanker in the Mediterranean to disembark on the coast of Sicily, after Malta refused them entry.
lead_paragraph: Italy on Wednesday allowed 102 migrants, mainly from North Africa and stranded on a tanker in the Mediterranean, to debark on the coast of Sicily.

headline.main: Italy: After Delays, Stranded Migrants Land
